# API & Server Action rules

Keep handlers **thin** — validate input, call modules in `src/lib/`, map errors to action results or HTTP responses. Server Actions in `src/app/actions/` are the primary mutation pattern; new REST endpoints only for cron, streaming, health, or auth.

## Auth

- Every Server Action starts with a guard: `auth()` + permission check (see `requireAdmin()` in `src/app/actions/admin.ts`, `requireHr()` in `src/lib/hr-auth.ts`).
- Every `/api/*` route enforces its own auth — middleware passes `/api/*` through.
- Cron routes: `isAuthorizedCronRequest(request)` from `src/lib/cron-auth.ts` (`CRON_SECRET` Bearer).
- Never import Prisma-backed auth in `middleware.ts` (edge) — it uses `src/lib/auth.config.ts` only.

## Validation

Manual `FormData` parsing (no Zod). Trim strings, validate required fields at the boundary, and return early on failure.

## Responses

- Server Actions return `{ error?: string }` for user-facing failures — do not throw to the client.
- Call `revalidatePath()` after mutations.
- API routes return `NextResponse.json(...)` with proper status codes; never return stack traces in production.

## Cron routes (`vercel.json`)

| Path | Schedule | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| `/api/cron/process-notifications` | `*/5 * * * *` | Deliver `NotificationOutbox` emails via Resend |
| `/api/cron/weekly-holiday-slack` | `0 7 * * 1` | Post weekly approved-leave digest to Slack |
| `/api/cron/import-sheet` | `*/30 * * * *` | Import Ops File Google Sheet into `GatewaySheetRecord` |

Collectors/processors live in `src/lib/` (`notifications/process.ts`, `holiday-weekly-digest.ts`, `sheets-import.ts`) — cron handlers just auth and delegate.

## Do NOT

- Put business rules inline in route handlers
- Skip auth on routes exposed to the internet
- Return stack traces to clients in production
